UNITED STATES of America ex rel. DARE BOK FUN, Next Friend and Brother of Dare Bok Dan, Relator-Appellant, v. DIRECTOR OF IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION AT THE PORT OF NEW YORK, Respondent-Appellee. No. 268. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 18, 1940. Jay Ahram Darwin, of New York City, for relator-appellant. John T. Cahill, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Jerome H. Doran, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Rockville Centre, N. Y., of counsel), for respondent-appellee.

Before SWAN, CLARK, and PATTERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed on opinion below, 32 F.Supp. 338.
